<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-01-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-01-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="690" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d690">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Choate</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-01-16"><hi rend="italic">January 16,
                                1900</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Ascertain and cable the status of American cargoes on the <hi rend="italic">Maria</hi>, the <hi rend="italic">Mashona</hi>, and
                            the <hi rend="italic">Beatrice</hi>, so Department may inform shippers
                            where their goods are and what portion of them are free.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hay.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>